{"authors":["Razon Yang"],"categories":["Image","Installation"],"pages":[{"authors":[{"title":"Razon Yang","url":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/authors/razonyang/"}],"categories":[{"title":"Image","url":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/categories/image/"}],"content":"Since v1.0.0-alpha.1, HBS supports much more image processing methods. Such as Crop, Fit and Fill images. You can also apply filters on an image.\nSee also Image Processing.\n","date":"July 8, 2022","img":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/news/2022/07/more-image-processing-methods/featured-sample.webp","lang":"en","langName":"English","largeImg":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/news/2022/07/more-image-processing-methods/featured-sample_huc6bcc14d597e300fd9ab4aae536c68a5_498412_500x0_resize_q75_h2_box_2.webp","permalink":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/news/2022/07/more-image-processing-methods/","series":[{"title":"News","url":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/series/news/"}],"smallImg":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/news/2022/07/more-image-processing-methods/featured-sample_huc6bcc14d597e300fd9ab4aae536c68a5_498412_180x0_resize_q75_h2_box_2.webp","tags":[{"title":"Crop","url":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/tags/crop/"},{"title":"Fit","url":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/tags/fit/"},{"title":"Fill","url":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/tags/fill/"},{"title":"Filters","url":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/tags/filters/"}],"title":"More Image Processing Methods"},{"authors":[],"categories":[],"content":"See also README.md.\n","date":"April 17, 2022","img":"","lang":"en","langName":"English","largeImg":"","permalink":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/blog/readme/","series":[],"smallImg":"","tags":[{"title":"README","url":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/tags/readme/"}],"title":"README"},{"authors":[],"categories":[],"content":"Written in Go, Hugo is an open source static site generator available under the Apache Licence 2.0. Hugo supports TOML, YAML and JSON data file types, Markdown and HTML content files and uses shortcodes to add rich content. Other notable features are taxonomies, multilingual mode, image processing, custom output formats, HTML/CSS/JS minification and support for Sass SCSS workflows.\nHugo makes use of a variety of open source projects including:\nhttps://github.com/yuin/goldmark https://github.com/alecthomas/chroma https://github.com/muesli/smartcrop https://github.com/spf13/cobra https://github.com/spf13/viper Hugo is ideal for blogs, corporate websites, creative portfolios, online magazines, single page applications or even a website with thousands of pages.\nHugo is for people who want to hand code their own website without worrying about setting up complicated runtimes, dependencies and databases.\nWebsites built with Hugo are extremely fast, secure and can be deployed anywhere including, AWS, GitHub Pages, Heroku, Netlify and any other hosting provider.\nLearn more and contribute on GitHub.\n","date":"February 28, 2019","img":"","lang":"en","langName":"English","largeImg":"","permalink":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/about/","series":[],"smallImg":"","tags":[],"title":"About"},{"authors":[],"categories":[{"title":"Installation","url":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/categories/installation/"}],"content":"This guide show you how to install on Arch Linux.\n","date":"January 1, 1","img":"","lang":"en","langName":"English","largeImg":"","permalink":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/docs/installation/linux/archlinux/","series":[{"title":"Guide","url":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/series/guide/"}],"smallImg":"","tags":[{"title":"Linux","url":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/tags/linux/"},{"title":"Arch Linux","url":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/tags/arch-linux/"}],"title":"Install on Arch Linux"},{"authors":[],"categories":[],"content":"","date":"January 1, 1","img":"","lang":"en","langName":"English","largeImg":"","permalink":"https://blog.zhsit.cn/contact/","series":[],"smallImg":"","tags":[],"title":"Contact Us"},{"authors":[],"categories":[],"content":"A fast, responsive and feature-rich Hugo theme for blog and documentations site.\n","date":"January 1, 1","img":"","lang":"en","langName":"English","largeImg":"","p